File: ANC Secretary-General Ace Magashule. JOHANNESBURG - ANC Secretary-General, Ace Magashule says he will step aside only if party branches ask him to. He has criticised the media for asking why he has not been removed yet. READ: Magashule supporters explain why they stand with the SG "This ANC is an organisation of the branches of the ANC and that is why I will respect the voices of branches.," Magashule said. 'If branches say I must step aside, I was elected by branches at the conference, I will go back to a special conference and if the branches say to me, comrade Magashule step aside, I will then do so." Magashule is facing 21 fraud, corruption, and money-laundering charges, linked to the R255-million Free State asbestos project. READ: Ace Magashule granted bail He has been released on R200,000 bail after appearing in the Bloemfontein Magistrate's Court. He is expected back in court in February.